   Stefan Lucks asks:
>   1. Are there results that show that Functions like MD5 ore SHS are secure
>      (under some reasonable cryptographic assumption)?
>   2. Are there one-way-hashfunctions that can be shown to be secure under
>      some reasonable cryptographic assumption?

  The answer to (1.) is No (to the best of my knowledge).
  The answer to (2.) is Yes.  See I. B. Damgard, "Collision Free Hash Functions
and Public Key Signature Schemes", EUROCRYPT '87, pp. 203-216.

